$ dbms_pipe

`dbms_pipe` allows two or more → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/session[sessions] to communicate with each other.

→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/pipe/purge[dbms_pipe.purge]

→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/pipe/send-receive[Most simple example: send and receive]

→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/pipe/perl[Read and write with Perl]

`dbms_pipe.unique_session_name` generates and returns a *unique pipe name*.

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/output[`dbms_output`]

  The → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/bin/rman[RMAN client (`$ORACLE_HOME/bin/rman`)] can be controlled with a
  → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/bin/rman#rman-client-pipe[pipe interface].

  Do not confuse `dbms_pipe` with the → development/databases/Oracle/PL-SQL/statements/pipe-row[`pipe row` statement]

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms
